<item>
            <title>[HBASE-17295] The namespace table has two regions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-17295</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From the codes, hbase namespace meta table should not allowed to be split.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;HRegion#checkSplit&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] checkSplit() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Can&apos;t split META
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.getRegionInfo().isMetaTable() ||
        TableName.NAMESPACE_TABLE_NAME.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.getRegionInfo().getTable())) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (shouldForceSplit()) {
        LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Cannot split meta region in HBase 0.20 and above&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      }
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//.....
&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But recently,  I see two namespace regions  in our production deployment. It may be cased by restarting when cluster is in certain state.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
